    <item>
      <title>Re: Petition to increase Barkspur Duration to 15 mins.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=druidbalance&amp;message.id=10611#M10611</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
Lluianae wrote:&lt;BR&gt;I understand why Prathun says that, since it is additive dps on top of what the raid is already executing and will further surpress regen such, with the combined total, would take AE rampers down much faster than intended. Don't forget since it stacks with Slot1 (that a mage can just mgb) and all other slot DSes from clickies/songs, factor in RDS dps (since its silly not to RDS AE rampers for extra damage), Prat is right saying it would be too much. Don't get me wrong, I love my damage shields, but note that he did say "in a matter of seconds" which is exagerated some, but assuming 25 people on a raid are taking ~4 ae ramp hits per AE ramp session at a constant, it would only take 4-5 AE ramp sessions just for 90k damage to happen (and in fact total melees on raids is likely higher than that in most cases).&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;I could understand that as well but the problem is it only answers a suggestion that was probably overblown to begin with.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Barkspur doesn't need a 15minute duration, a much lower but better duration would just as fine.&amp;nbsp; Hell adding another 6seconds would go a long way since it makes foci and aa apply.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;But&amp;nbsp;barkspur is 300mana, 210ds with a max 8hits (so 1680dmg unresistable but unmodable dmg) 3 sec cast time 13sec recast...&amp;nbsp; Offhand, what's the bonus of this spell? Low mana, unresistable dmg, fast cast time -- how does that compare though?&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Dmg per cast: Barkspur 1680 | Dawnstrike 2125 (+mods and crits)&amp;nbsp;|&amp;nbsp;Solstice strike 2201 (+mods and crits) | Ancient glacier frost 2042 (+mods and crits)... no bonus for barkspur over any other spell.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Dmg per mana: Barkspur 1680/300 = 5.6 | Dawnstrike 2125/482 = 4.5 ... Dawnstrike needs a 25% bonus to be as effecient as barkspur, max crit rate at the time was&amp;nbsp;over 20% iirc,&amp;nbsp;dragon fire would avg out to 25%, dawnstrike's bonus by itself avg'd out to a 12.5% bonus iirc. | Solstice strike 2201/494 = 4.45 .. same note as Dawnstrike | AGF&amp;nbsp; 2042/405 = 5 .. a 10% mod would make agf rival barkspur's mana effieciency.... Any bonus barkspur has on paper is quickly lost in practice.&amp;nbsp; Again no real advantage to casting that over another spell.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Cast time: 3sec with a 23% haste brings the cast time down to 2.3sec cast time.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Dawnstrike 4.7&amp;nbsp; Solstice strike 4.2&amp;nbsp; Ancient glacier frost 4.3 ... as a form of quick dmg the difference is 2 to 2.4 seconds.&amp;nbsp; 8 max hits would suggest it would at best take 2 rounds on a mob that quads and that there be no misses at all under 2seconds to beat a nuke as a form of fast dmg.&amp;nbsp; Again no advantage for barkspur in practice.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Resistability... Barkspur Unresistable | Dawnstrike + solstice vs. fire (can be debuffed 112pts) | AGV vs. cold (could be debuffed 55pts at the time) .. Advantage technically goes to barkspur, how ever in practice the instances where resists are really issue for a class able to debuff vs. their primary elements are limited to mobs that have very strong resists to both fire and cold... Offhand that's like M'sha's, Txevu Zun, PVP, someone mentioned an mpg trial though I never really noticed that.. all in all resists normally aren't that much of an issue so it ends up again, not that much of a practical advantage for barkspur.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;So how else can Barkspur be usefull outside of pvp and txevu zun?&amp;nbsp; If the dev's had a specific plan for it I'd love to hear it (I believe the guy that made the spell isn't around anymore though?) but as a player the only viable use I could see for it in normal grping situations is as concurrent dmg.&amp;nbsp; It does it's dmg over time and doesn't require a mob in camp to be cast so it could be put onto the tank before the mob gets to camp and hopefully do it's dmg as the druid debuffs / starts to nuke.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;To do that well though you have to cast it 5 secs before the mob arrives.. earlier if you want to cast debuffs as the mob is inc.&amp;nbsp; So say you're really on the ball with timing, you cast bark spur -&amp;gt; 2.25sec gem refresh -&amp;gt; hand of ro on the mob as it's inc (2.5sec) -&amp;gt; 2.25sec gem refresh -&amp;gt; Mob is in camp, tank picks it up and you can start nuking right away for further debuff... but take that situation, by the time the mob is in camp and on the tank 7secs have past.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Barkspur lasts 18seconds so 11secs left on it.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Lets say your avg mob has a 50% hit rate (the raid parses on my guilds boards offhand look like they lean more towards 40% so that should be more than fair), that would mean it'd take 16swings to actually use all of barkspur.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 4 rounds if a mob quads, 6 if it triples, 8 if it doubles.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; That means those mobs would need a 2.75s / 1.8sec / and 1.38s dly between rounds respectively to fully utilize barkspur as concurrent dmg.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; How likely really are those situations in grps?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The easy solution to that is to up the duration on it... does it have to be 15minutes? no.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 15mins for 300 mana is dumb.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; If by chance you cast it and no mobs are inc for 2minutes + for some reason you're not going to mourn losing 300mana after all that time.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Ideally I think the duration should end up being around 48sec (the original 18sec +30sec leeway time) to a minute.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Bumping it up to 24seconds&amp;nbsp; will go a long way b/c then aa and foci can apply to it that would in effect make it's duration 7 ticks/42sec.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Ultimately I'd say at the very least make it 30seconds duration.. That would mean any druid with the appropriate aa's and I believe any&amp;nbsp;extention mod would get 48seconds (note: mage's equivalent spell has 24seconds + mod to do half the hits required of barkspur) duration on barkspur.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; A druid with the very best duration would have barkspur last 54seconds.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;If that worst case scenario druid &amp;nbsp;tried using barkspur like prathun suggested he'd at max be able to keep it on&amp;nbsp;4 ppl till engage, and by that time it'd be close to wearing off of the first.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; So at worst if one of the few negliable ae ramp mobs where to hit all 4 before it wore off on them all that would be 6720 extra dmg from out of combat casting single panther should be about 4k dmg so grp panther would easily out do that already in terms of precedent).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Once the mob is engaged casting nukes becomes much better dps.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;If nothing else it just doesn't make sense that our spell be 18secs to get 8 hits while mages be 24 to 32secs to&amp;nbsp; get 4 hits.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; You'd think double the hits should require double the time.&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
