      <description>The only real use I've found for Barkspur in a group setting is when all three of these conditions are present: 1) I'm main healer, &lt;u&gt;&lt;i&gt;and&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/u&gt; 2) the group is low on dps, &lt;u&gt;&lt;i&gt;and&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/u&gt; 3) every mob 'enrages' (e.g. ashengate). In such a scenario, stacking the extra DS helps compensate for the tank turning off attack during the last tick or two of combat.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Otherwise the spell is lackluster -- which means, 99.9% of the time. Honestly, if any of those 3 conditions isn't true, the spell isn't worth keeping memmed. I.E. If I'm not the main healer, I can nuke; if we have plenty of dps in the group, the tank's doesn't matter as much; and if the mobs don't enrage, there's no added urgency to get the mob dead when it gets low health.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I would much rather have a .5 second nuke similar to Sting of the Queen. Now that spell is a nice quick way to get past an enraging mob ... and what's funny is how, despite how much some shaman have tried to downplay that spell, *every* shaman I've grouped with has already made it a habit of casting every time it pops, quite easily between their other spells. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Regards,&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Mahzz&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
